The paper proposes a new framework for generating discrete data using an adversarial approach. This falls under the category of machine learning and specifically generative models. The paper focuses on text generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) falling under the category of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are commonly used in NLP and fall under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of normalization and convergence properties, which are common topics in neural networks and optimization, falling under the categories of neural networks (NE) and computer vision (CV), respectively. Therefore, cs.NE and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories.
